  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "Decades on, Eisenhorn is older, harder, and openly using a bound daemonhost — Cherubael — as a working tool. His old enemy Pontius Glaw, presumed contained, escapes his iron prison with help from a Mechanicus reclamator named Pater Sinjet. The pursuit drags Eisenhorn through the agri-world of Durer and the ice-tomb of Spaeton House on Gudrun, and costs him half his retinue. He closes the case but loses Fischig to puritan denunciation, and Bequin to a stasis injury that will not unwind. The book is an obituary in the voice of the obituary's author — he is the man he once would have arrested, and he writes the record himself because he no longer trusts any other archivist to do it.",
